  "text": "## Rust-Servo Shared Style System Discovery\n\n### Servo Style System (sg-evals/servo--be6a2f99)\n\nServo does not contain local `components/style/` or `components/selectors/` directories. Instead, it depends on external Stylo crates from the `github.com/servo/stylo` repository at commit `3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827`.\n\n**Main Cargo.toml Dependencies (Servo/Cargo.toml lines 160, 169, 178-183):**\n- `selectors = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `servo_arc = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `stylo = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `stylo_atoms = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `stylo_config = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `stylo_dom = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `stylo_malloc_size_of = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n- `stylo_traits = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }`\n\n**Style System Integration in Servo:**\n- `tests/unit/style/lib.rs` - Test suite for the style system\n- `components/script_bindings/build.rs` (line 18) - Uses `DEP_SERVO_STYLE_CRATE_OUT_DIR` environment variable to access the style crate's generated output, including `css-properties.json`\n\n### Rust Proc Macro Bridge (sg-evals/rust--01f6ddf7)\n\nThe proc_macro bridge, which enables Servo to use Rust's procedural macro infrastructure, is defined in the Rust compiler:\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs` - Main proc_macro library crate. Contains `is_available()` function (line 88) to detect if proc_macro infrastructure is available\n- `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs` - Core bridge implementation defining the RPC API between proc macro clients and server using the `with_api!` macro (lines 48-100+). This macro generates type-safe APIs for communicating between the proc macro crate and the compiler front-end using C ABI buffers and unique integer handles\n- `compiler/rustc_proc_macro/Cargo.toml` - Wrapper crate that points to `library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs` (line 13: `path = \"../../library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs\"`)\n\n### Rust-Servo Integration\n\nThe Rust compiler explicitly tests Servo's selectors crate:\n\n**File: src/tools/cargotest/main.rs (lines 72-83)**\n- Servo repository test entry: `https://github.com/servo/servo` at commit `785a344e32db58d4e631fd3cae17fd1f29a721ab`\n- Tests only the `selectors` package (line 79: `packages: &[\"selectors\"]`)\n- Comment (lines 77-78): \"Only test Stylo a.k.a. Quantum CSS, the parts of Servo going into Firefox. This takes much less time to build than all of Servo and supports stable Rust.\"\n\n### Shared Code Architecture\n\nThe connection between Rust and Servo is established through:\n1. **Stylo (Style System)**: External crates hosted at `github.com/servo/stylo` shared by both Servo and Rust\n2. **Proc Macro Bridge**: Rust's `library/proc_macro/src/bridge/` provides the infrastructure that Servo build scripts use\n3. **Testing Integration**: Rust's cargotest includes Servo's selectors crate to ensure stability of the shared CSS selector engine\n\nThe proc_macro bridge uses an RPC mechanism with C ABI buffers to allow safe communication between proc macro crates (like those built by Servo) and the Rust compiler, enabling Servo's build process to leverage Rust's procedural macro system."
}

